value.Description: Elementary Stochastic Processes (MA/STAT 490) is an introduction to stochastic processes. The main topics of study will be Markov chains (discrete and continuous time), Poisson processes and renewal processes. If time allows, we will also cover topics such as Brownian motion, Martingales, and Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC). The processes studied have numerous applications for probabilistic modelling in computer science, physics, biology, electrical engineering and many other fields., MA/STAT 41600 and Linear Algebra (MA 26500 or MA 35100) are prerequisites
